# Trivy CRITICAL allowlist for penpot (Cocoon AI base fork).
#
# Per cai-portal ADR 0003 + foreign-apps rule. Allowlist-by-exception.
# Every entry MUST carry a comment block: package, date added, why
# the CVE is unexploitable, upstream tracking link.
#
# Empty = baseline clean. CI's Trivy job in deploy.yml fails on any
# unannotated CRITICAL.
#
# Tenant forks inherit this baseline; tenant-specific exceptions can
# layer on top (commits on tenant-fork main, not rebased here).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Frontend image (nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged:1.30.0) transitive libs.
# These CVEs are in libraries that the frontend's nginx never invokes:
# the frontend serves static SPA files and proxies HTTP/WebSocket
# requests over plain TCP to the backend container — no DTLS handshake,
# no SSH client. Added 2026-05-15.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Package: libgnutls30t64 3.8.9-3+deb13u2 (Debian 13 trixie)
# Date: 2026-05-15
# Why unexploitable: nginx in the frontend image performs no DTLS
#   negotiation. TLS termination is upstream at the ALB; nginx-to-backend
#   is plaintext HTTP on the docker compose network. gnutls is pulled
#   in transitively but never instantiated for a DTLS session.
# Upstream tracking: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-33845
CVE-2026-33845

# Package: libgnutls30t64 3.8.9-3+deb13u2
# Date: 2026-05-15
# Why unexploitable: GnuTLS NUL-byte auth-bypass requires the frontend
#   to invoke GnuTLS for certificate-based auth, which it does not (see
#   above; TLS terminates at the ALB). The bypass path is not reachable
#   in the nginx static-serve / HTTP-proxy code path.
# Upstream tracking: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42010
CVE-2026-42010

# Package: libssh2-1t64 1.11.1-1
# Date: 2026-05-15
# Why unexploitable: the frontend image runs only nginx, which is
#   compiled without ssh-related modules and never spawns an SSH client.
#   libssh2 is installed as a transitive dep of unrelated tooling that
#   isn't invoked at runtime. Integer overflow path requires calling
#   into libssh2's username/password parsing — no caller in the runtime
#   image.
# Upstream tracking: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-7598
CVE-2026-7598
